post_text:
OCS families-

After much thought and deliberation as a district, Onsted Community Schools is moving the start of school for students from Monday, August 31, 2020 to Tuesday, September 8, 2020.

This change was determined to be the prudent course of action to ensure our OCS staff is prepared to welcome students back to campus. We will use the additional days of professional development to prepare our staff around our new instructional strategies and safety protocols.

We thank you again for your patience and understanding as we continue to prepare for the start of our school year. An updated calendar will be shared and posted on the website in the coming days.

post_text:
Information on Filing a Petition for School Board Candidacy

Please see the following information for anyone interested in running for the school board.

OCS has (3) six-year terms up for election in November:

The deadline for candidates to file is on or before July 21st, 2020, by 4:00 pm.
Candidates can file School District Nominating Petitions for a non-refundable $100.00 filing fee.
A minimum of 6 signatures and a maximum of 20 signatures is needed to qualify.

Filing paperwork is available at the Cambridge Township Clerk’s Office.

Cambridge Township Hall
9990 M 50
Onsted, MI 49265
(517) 467-2104

You may also contact the office of Roxann Holloway for additional filing information or questions.

Steve Head, Superintendent
Onsted Community Schools

We are still working on graduation ceremonies at this time and are looking at a mid to late July date to honor the Class of 2020. More details to follow when they become available.

Go Cats!!

post_text:
Onsted Community Schools Press Release on Outside Facilities

Lenawee County commissioners issued an executive order Monday to further mitigate the congregation of people in public places.

The order closes park and recreation areas, such as playgrounds, track facilities, tennis, volleyball and basketball courts, softball and baseball fields, gazebos and similar areas that “encourage close contact with others,” according to a news release.

This includes both public parks and playground and recreation areas at apartment complexes, schools and private property where access is permitted beyond immediate family members.
The order does not and is not intended to keep people from walking, cycling, hiking or running in public. These activities are still allowed, but social distancing guidelines should be followed.

We apologize for the inconvenience, but the health and safety of our community is the top priority.

Steve Head, Superintendent
Onsted Community Schools

Free Breakfast/Lunch Program Pick up for Week of April 6th and Beyond

OCS will be offering free breakfast/lunch for students ages 18 and under once again next week. 5 days’ worth of meals can be picked up for each child. Meals can be picked up Monday, April 6th and every Monday afterward until further notice. Pickup will be between 11 am and 1 pm in HS parking lot.

Meals will be available for pickup Monday’s only moving forward on a weekly basis.

Please enter the HS parking lot and drive through the HS lot towards the track and pull up in front of the Athletic Office/Fitness Center entrance facing east. Directions on how to proceed will be shared from there by our volunteers.

If possible, please bring any boxes or bags to assist us in packing the meals. Thank you!

Additional information regarding COVID‐19 is available via the following links:
www.lenawee.mi.us/917/2019‐Novel‐Coronavirus
www.coronavirus.gov
www.michigan.gov/coronavirus

Steve Head, Superintendent
Onsted Community Schools

Free Breakfast/Lunch Program During the Mandatory Shutdown:

OCS is offering a free meal program (breakfast/lunch) available to all OCS students ages 18 and under during the mandated shutdown. 7 days’ worth of meals can be picked up for each child. The food will be available for pick-up at the HS Auditeria entrance.

We are changing the days and hours of availability based on the current situation.

Food pickup will be available Tuesday/Wednesday this week from 11 am-1 pm. There will be no Thursday/Friday pickups.

Food pickup for the weeks of March 23rd and March 30th will Monday and Wednesday from 11 am-1 pm at the HS Auditeria Entrance.

If other arrangements need to be made, please contact Brenda Hubbard at 467-5500 or by email at hubbard.b@onstedschools.us.

This information will also be available on the district website. If you have any additional questions or concerns please contact Brenda Hubbard.

Thank you!

It’s NOT too late to get into a preschool program for this current school year! If your child’s birth date is between 9/2/14 & 12/1/15 they could be eligible for our free, state funded, preschool program.

-Research based, hands-on curriculum
-Highly Qualified Teachers
-Three family-style meals served each day

-Play-based learning focusing on:
-Social Emotional
-Cognitive
-Mathematics
-Language
-Literacy

If interested, please go to www.lenaweefreepreschools.org and fill out the interest form or call 517-264-5324 to determine if your child is eligible. Deadline approaching fast! Don’t delay!

Onsted Elementary School
October 30, 2019 at 4:07 PM ·

As most of you know, Thursday is usually an exciting time for our students but it can be a bit stressful for families. One way we are hoping to help is with a parking option. Most families will be able to find parking in the gravel lot or in the church parking lot across from the elementary school. We also have reserved parking downtown at Borchardt's Market and our transportation department will have a bus to transport your family to the elementary school.

We are going to offer a bus shuttle from Borchardt’s Market to the school at 7:30, 7:45, and 8:00 in the morning.

We will also have three bus deliveries to shuttle families back to their cars. Pick up will be directly in front of the elementary school in the drop off/pick up zone at 9:30, 9:45, and 10:00.

In the morning, students need to be dressed in their costumes. Our parade begins at 8:15 and we don't want anyone to miss out!

All families will enter through the gym door by Mrs. Holm‘s classroom.

Costume reminders: no masks, blood, face paint, weapons of any kind. Thank you!

We also have reserved parking downtown at Borchardt's Market and our transportation department will have a bus to transport your family to the elementary school.

We are going to offer a bus shuttle from Borchardt’s Market to the school at 7:30, 7:45, and 8:00 in the morning.

We will also have three bus deliveries to shuttle families back to their cars. Pick up will be directly in front of the elementary school in the drop off/pick up zone at 9:30, 9:45, and 10:00.

In the morning, students need to be dressed in their costumes. Our parade begins at 8:15 and we don't want anyone to miss out!

All families will enter through the gym door by Mrs. Holm‘s classroom.

Costume reminders: no masks, blood, face paint, weapons of any kind. Thank you!

ATTENTION HS STUDENTS!

February 22nd, that is ONE WEEK from today, will be the LAST DAY to purchase a 2018/2019 yearbook! After that date, there will be no opportunity to buy a yearbook.

To purchase a yearbook, follow the steps below:
1. Go to onstedschools.us
2. Under the 'Our Schools' tab at the top right hand side of the page, click 'High School'
3. Scroll to the bottom of the page. There you will find a link to 'Jostens', click on it.
4. From there you will be redirected to the Jostens website. Click the option 'Click to Order Your Yearbook'
5. Follow the steps from there!

Buying a yearbook is important, so do not wait any longer!

For any questions, contact walkerl@onstedschools.us

GO WILDCATS!
